The council says working and congregating close to each other makes them more exposed. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBUEG - The Minerals Council of South Africa says miners are highly vulnerable to infectious diseases. The council says working and congregating close to each other makes them more exposed. WATCH: Doctor of SA's first coronavirus patient speaks It's released a nine-point plan that will mitigate the risk of coronavirus. This includes Employee Education and Health Promotion, as well as Health worker readiness campaigns. READ: What you need to know about coronavirus On Thursday, South Africa confirmed its first case of coronavirus. A 38-year-old man from KwaZulu-Natal was confirmed as the first South African to be infected with COVID-19. Watch the video above